Question: Do you think age restrictions on drinking are effective?
Answer:
In my experience, no. I have seen enough underage people under the influence to think that age restrictions are not effective. The problem is that alcohol is too easily acquired. Parents have bars in their houses. ID checking is the only effective way to prevent underaged persons from getting alcohol, and it is too easily sidestepped. And I don't think it makes people want to drink any less, knowing that they can't.